text: Guaminí Partido is a partido in the west of Buenos Aires Province in Argentina. The provincial subdivision has a population of about 11,000 inhabitants in an area of , and its capital city is Guaminí, which is from Buenos Aires. ==Economy== The economy of Guaminí partido is dominated by the cultivation of wheat, maize, soya beans, sunflowers, alfalfa, sorghum and oats. Other industries include beef and dairy farming and related farming services. ==Settlements== * Arroyo Venado * Casbas * Garré * Guaminí * Huanguelén * Laguna Alsina Category:1886 establishments in Argentina Category:Partidos of Buenos Aires Province
